AmRest Is Close to Buy Spain’s Restauravia, Expansion Reports

-- B y   M a n u e l   B a i g o r r i
-- 
2011-02-11T08:46:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-11/amrest-is-close-to-buy-spain-s-restauravia-expansion-reports.html
Poland’s  AmRest Holdings SE  is close
to acquiring Restauravia, Spain’s fifth-biggest restaurant
business with 130 restaurants, for 205 million euros ($278
million) in cash,  Expansion  reported, citing people in the
industry it didn’t identify.  The amount paid by AmRest for Restauravia, which is
controlled by the venture-capital firm Corpfin Capital, equals
about 8.5 times earnings before interest, taxes depreciation and
amortization, the newspaper said.  Restauravia and AmRest operate KFC restaurants in Spain and
central and eastern  Europe , respectively. AmRest’s plans include
expanding Restauravia’s brands to other European countries, the
newspaper added.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Manuel Baigorri in Madrid at 
 mbaigorri@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Angela Cullen at 
